Hometown: Ogallala

post_text:
We appreciate all the hard work our students have put into their school work during this time away from school. However, not all of the learning that has occurred in these past few weeks has been in our traditional school subjects. There have been many learning/service opportunities that our students are taking advantage of. We are proud of all of you for making the most of your time.

Last week, we asked students to send us examples of outside the school day projects that they have been working on. Here are a some of the pictures that have been submitted! Great to see the work ethic and service to the community in these projects. Madison Cheleen, Ryan Cheleen, Isabelle Reichman, and Ethan Reichman have been working on 4-H projects, building planters, making masks to donate, construction projects, and cleaning out bins.

We would love to feature pictures of more of these learning opportunities, so please send photos in to Mr. Spencer or Mr. Ford. Keep up the great work!

South Platte certified and support staff will meet on Tuesday at 9:00am to be updated on the school closing and make plans for future engaging enrichment activities for students.

On Tuesday, March 17 students will be allowed to stop by the school between 11:00am and 1:00pm to pick up any personal items, books or electronics.

Starting Friday, March 20th, the school will be providing sack lunches for any enrolled students. Please call the school to get added to this list. Sack lunches will be available for pick up at the school, and the bus pick-up sites. Brule activity center, Ogallala Library, Chappell Library, and Lodgepole Library. Friday‚Äôs lunch will be ham and cheese sandwiches. Time of delivery and next weeks menu will be available later this week.

Please contact the school is you do not have access to internet. We will be working to make arrangements to ensure that all students have access to enrichment opportunities provided by our staff.

Thank you again for you patience and understanding in these days of uncertainty.

Good luck to the HS and JH CC runners as they compete at Chase County today (9/12) at 3:30pm! We are looking forward to more personal bests! Last week Brittany Hensley and Britany Lofton placed in their respective races!

Also good luck to HS VB as they compete today (9/12) against Wallace starting with JV at 4:00pm followed by Varsity. They also play Hay Springs tomorrow (9/13) with JV starting at 3:30 and varsity to follow. They will also play at the GC tourney on Saturday (9/14). That bracket is attached to this post. The JV games have yet to be posted for Saturday.

Finally, the HS Football team will play tomorrow 9/13 against Hay Springs here at South Platte. Good luck to the boys!

Numerous PR‚Äôs for all teams. The JH boys and Girls had one of their best meets of the year. The girls also finished 2nd at the MAC track meet today!

All of the hard work these athletes and coaches are putting in is paying off. Keep getting better every day!!
